07:46 <@cjdelisle> https://github.com/cjdelisle/preemptive-lock/ <-- weekend project  
07:47 <@cjdelisle> I was able to prove that it can't deadlock so that leaves the obvious: thread dropped a lock without unlocking it  
07:47 <@cjdelisle> which is also easy to fix by using lock wrappers that unlock in their finalize() method.  
07:48 <vmassol> cjdelisle: seems you've had fun over the weekend!  
07:48 <@cjdelisle> It was an older project, it's part of filesystem attachments, I just formalized it and wrote a (non-academic) paper.  
07:49 <@cjdelisle> Pretty exciting since I don't think anyone has solved that problem that well before.  
07:49 <vmassol> brb breakfast  
07:50 <@cjdelisle> see ya

11:14 <jamesxu> I want to add some html script into page editor page, and I found the edit.vm under /webapps/template/edit.vm which maps to the struts-config.xml, I add something to this vm file, restart the server, but nothing happened, I even delete edit.vm file, nothing happened either  
11:14 <vmassol> jamesxu: btw you don't need to restart when editing vm files (except for macros.vm)  
11:14 <vmassol> what happens is that skin has probably overriden the vm you edited  
11:14 <vmassol> so you should edit  the vm in the skin rather than the base vm one in templates/  
11:15 <vmassol> (skins are in the skins/  webapp dir when deployed)  
11:15 <jamesxu> I see, so if I want to edit page, I have to edit page right  
11:16 <jamesxu> but in struts-config.xml, actions maps to /templates/\*.vm  
11:16 <jamesxu> another problem, there are many skins in the skin dir  
11:17 <vmassol> there should be only 3  
11:17 <jamesxu> if I change one of them, how about the other ones  
11:17 <lucaa1> has joined #xwiki  
11:17 <lucaa> has quit  
11:17 <vmassol> well skins are not supposed to override the common vms normally  
11:18 <vmassol> the reason the colbri skin overrides quite a lot is because we did a lot of rewrtie but haven't ported that back into base templates which is bad  
11:18 <jamesxu> for example, I add some new functions to one page, do I have to modify all the three skins?  
11:19 <jamesxu> ok, could you tell me xwiki how to config skins, and recoganize them?

16:00 <+lucaa> hi guys  
16:00 <+lucaa> I just built enterprise on my machine  
16:00 <+lucaa> and I have a strange behaviour  
16:00 <+lucaa> I have 2 oldcore jars in WEB-INF/lib  
16:01 <vmassol> lucaa: it's probabl the issue we discussed  
16:01 <+lucaa> I didn't follow  
16:01 <+lucaa> is there a report on jira or smth?  
16:02 <+lucaa> where  I can read more about?  
16:02 <vmassol> I want to fix it with http://jira.xwiki.org/jira/browse/XWIKI-6581  
16:02 <vmassol> I had it half done when I was diverged to fix the clustering issue  
16:02 <+lucaa> ah  
16:02 <+lucaa> and because of that there's this odd issue  
16:02 <+lucaa> but then, how reliable is the enterprise war?  
16:03 <+lucaa> anyway, I'll just startup my tomcat and see  
16:03 <+lucaa> however, it's not the same version, maybe there somewhere there's an issue  
16:03 <+lucaa> ls -al | grep oldcore  
16:03 <+lucaa> -rw-r--r-- 1 lucaa lucaa  2467935 2011-05-09 15:42 xwiki-platform-oldcore-3.1-20110509.130645-71.jar  
16:04 <+lucaa> -rw-r--r-- 1 lucaa lucaa  2467937 2011-05-09 11:15 xwiki-platform-oldcore-3.1-SNAPSHOT.jar  
16:04 <vmassol> it's almost the same...  
16:04 <vmassol> what happens is that you've built one locally and then the other one is retrived from ther emote repo  
16:04 <vmassol> one dep comes from the platform war  
16:05 <vmassol> and the other one from the enterprise war's pom.xml deps  
16:05 <vmassol> which draw the oldcore transitively  
16:05 <vmassol> (because for maven the war is an opaque blob)  
16:07 <+lucaa> right  
16:09 <vmassol> cjdelisle: there seems to be a branch named xwiki-3.1M1 in xwiki-commons  
16:10 <vmassol> it doesn't seem right since 3.1M1 has been released already  
16:10 <@cjdelisle> looking  
16:10 <@cjdelisle> nope, you're seeing things  
16:10 <@cjdelisle> ;)  
16:11 <vmassol> could it be because it existed at some point so my local repo has kept it?  
16:11 <@cjdelisle> actually it's on your local machine, even after a branch is removed from the upstream you keep your local version.  
16:11 <@cjdelisle> yup  
16:11 <vmassol> hmm so how do I "sync"?  
16:12 <@cjdelisle> http://kparal.wordpress.com/2011/04/15/git-tip-of-the-day-pruning-stale-remote-tracking-branches/  
16:12 <@cjdelisle> that might be what you're looking for.  
16:13 <vmassol> thanks, reading  
16:13 <@cjdelisle> I myself just used branch -d  
16:14 <vmassol> perfect thanks
